# SLDS Global Styling Hooks Reference
All `--slds-g-*` variables are immutable, centrally managed by Salesforce, and should not be reassigned in component code.

## Color Hooks

### Surface Colors
- Foundational background layers
- `--slds-g-color-surface-1`: Primary background surface
- `--slds-g-color-surface-2`: Elevated or alternate background layer

### Surface Container Colors
- Containers that sit on top of surfaces (e.g., cards)
- `--slds-g-color-surface-container-1`: Default container background
- `--slds-g-color-surface-container-2`: Slightly elevated container
- `--slds-g-color-surface-container-3`: Higher elevation container

### On-Surface Colors
- Text/icons placed on surface or container
- `--slds-g-color-on-surface-1`: Text/icon on surface level 1
- `--slds-g-color-on-surface-2`: Text/icon on surface level 2
- `--slds-g-color-on-surface-3`: Text/icon on surface level 3

### Border Colors (Neutral)
- Visual separation or outline
- `--slds-g-color-border-1`: Light neutral border for non-interactive elements
- `--slds-g-color-border-2`: Darker neutral border for interactive elements

### Accent Colors
- Emphasize elements or actions
- `--slds-g-color-accent-1`: Primary accent color
- `--slds-g-color-accent-2`: Alternate accent tone
- `--slds-g-color-accent-3`: Stronger/darker accent tone

### Accent Container Colors
- Background containers that hold text/icons on top of accents
- `--slds-g-color-accent-container-1`: Primary accent container
- `--slds-g-color-accent-container-2`: Alternate accent container
- `--slds-g-color-accent-container-3`: High-emphasis accent container

### On-Accent Colors
- Text/icons that appear on top of an accent container
- `--slds-g-color-on-accent-1`: Text/icon color on accent container level 1

### Border Accent Colors
- Borders using brand accent hues
- `--slds-g-color-border-accent-1`: Light border accent
- `--slds-g-color-border-accent-2`: Medium border accent
- `--slds-g-color-border-accent-3`: Strong border accent

### Feedback: Error
- For errors and alerts
- `--slds-g-color-error-1`: Text/icon error color
- `--slds-g-color-error-container-1`: Background error container
- `--slds-g-color-error-container-2`: Elevated error container
- `--slds-g-color-on-error-1`: Text/icon on error background
- `--slds-g-color-border-error-1`: Border for subtle error indication
- `--slds-g-color-border-error-2`: Border for interactive error components

### Feedback: Success
- `--slds-g-color-success-1`: Text/icon success color
- `--slds-g-color-success-container-1`: Success container
- `--slds-g-color-success-container-2`: Elevated success container
- `--slds-g-color-on-success-1`: Text/icon on success container
- `--slds-g-color-on-success-2`: Alternate text/icon on success
- `--slds-g-color-border-success-1`: Border for success messaging

### Feedback: Warning
- `--slds-g-color-warning-1`: Warning foreground color
- `--slds-g-color-warning-container-1`: Background warning container
- `--slds-g-color-on-warning-1`: Text/icon color for warning
- `--slds-g-color-border-warning-1`: Border color for warning indication

### Feedback: Info
- `--slds-g-color-info-1`: Informational text/icon
- `--slds-g-color-info-container-1`: Info background
- `--slds-g-color-on-info-1`: Info text/icon on background

### Feedback: Disabled
- `--slds-g-color-disabled-1`: Text/icon disabled
- `--slds-g-color-disabled-2`: Subtle disabled state
- `--slds-g-color-disabled-container-1`: Disabled background
- `--slds-g-color-disabled-container-2`: Alternate disabled container
- `--slds-g-color-on-disabled-1`: Text/icon on disabled container
